#      10 
def prepare_train_set(path_to_csv_files, session_length=10):
    
    f_list = glob(os.path.join(path_to_csv_files, '*.csv'))
    data = []
    users = {}
    
    #        (data) 
    #         (users)
    for i in tqdm_notebook(range(len(f_list)), desc='reading', unit = 'user'):
        user_id = int(f_list[i].split('\\')[-1].split('.')[0][-4:])
        user_sites = [sites[1].rstrip() for sites in 
                      [file.split(',') for file in open(f_list[i])][1:]
                     ]
        data.extend(user_sites)
        users[user_id] = len(user_sites)

    #    {site: number_visits}
    dict_counter = dict.fromkeys(data, 0)
    for i in tqdm_notebook(data, desc='creating dict', unit = 'rec', unit_scale=True):
        dict_counter[i] += 1
    
    #     
    dict_counter = sorted(dict_counter.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
    
    #     {site: (code, number_visits)}
    site_freq = dict(zip([x[0] for x in dict_counter], 
                         enumerate([x[1] for x in dict_counter], start=1)))
    
    ####    ####
    start = 0 #       data
    shift = 0 #      
    #   : n - , m - 
    n = int(sum(np.ceil(np.array([x[1] for x in users.items()])/session_length)))
    m = session_length + 1
    res = np.zeros(n * m, dtype='int32').reshape(n, m) #   

    #      
    for user in tqdm_notebook(users.items(), desc='creating matrix', unit = 'user'):
        end = start + user[1] #       data
        user_sites = data[start:end] #   
        
        #       
        for i in range(int(np.ceil(len(user_sites)/session_length))):
            sess = user_sites[i * session_length: (i + 1) * session_length]
            sites_id = [site_freq[x][0] for x in sess]
            #    ;  ,  
            if len(sites_id) == session_length:
                sites_id.append(user[0])
            else:
                sites_id.extend([0]*(session_length - len(sites_id)))
                sites_id.append(user[0])
            res[shift + i] = sites_id
        #     data   res   
        start = end
        shift = shift + int(np.ceil((user[1])/session_length)) 

    #    DataFrame (  )
    res = pd.DataFrame(res)
    res.columns = [x[0] + str(x[1]) 
                   for x in zip(['site'] * session_length, range(1, session_length + 1))
                  ] + ['user_id']

    return res, site_freq

def prepare_sparse_train_set_window(path_to_csv_files, site_freq_path, 
                                    session_length=10, window_size=10):
   
    f_list = glob(os.path.join(path_to_csv_files, '*.csv'))
    data = []
    users = {}
    #      
    with open(site_freq_path, 'rb') as site_freq_pkl:
        site_freq = pickle.load(site_freq_pkl)

    #        (data) 
    #         (users)
    for i in tqdm_notebook(range(len(f_list)), desc='reading', unit = 'user'):
        user_id = int(f_list[i].split('\\')[-1].split('.')[0][-4:])
        user_sites = [sites[1].rstrip() for sites in 
                      [file.split(',') for file in open(f_list[i])][1:]
                     ]
        data.extend(user_sites)
        users[user_id] = len(user_sites)

    ####    ####
    start = 0 #       data
    shift = 0 #      
    #   : n - , m - 
    n = int(sum(np.ceil(np.array([x[1] for x in users.items()])/window_size)))
    m = session_length + 1
    res = np.zeros(n * m, dtype='int32').reshape(n, m) #   

    #      
    for user in tqdm_notebook(users.items(), desc='creating matrix', unit = 'user'):
        end = start + user[1] #       data
        user_sites = data[start:end] #   

        #       
        for i in range(int(np.ceil(len(user_sites)/window_size))):
            sess = user_sites[i * window_size: i  * window_size + session_length]
            sites_id = [site_freq[x][0] for x in sess]
            #    ;  ,  
            if len(sites_id) == session_length:
                sites_id.append(user[0])
            else:
                sites_id.extend([0]*(session_length - len(sites_id)))
                sites_id.append(user[0])
            res[shift + i] = sites_id
        #     data   res   
        start = end
        shift = shift + int(np.ceil((user[1])/window_size)) 

    #    DataFrame (  )
    res = pd.DataFrame(res)
    res.columns = [x[0] + str(x[1]) 
                   for x in zip(['site'] * session_length, range(1, session_length + 1))
                  ] + ['user_id']

    X, y = res.iloc[:, :-1].values, res.iloc[:, -1].values
    X_sparse = csr_matrix(
        (np.ones(X.size, dtype='int8'), 
         X.ravel(), 
         range(0, X.size + session_length, session_length)
        ))[:,1:]

    return X_sparse, y

#     GridSearchCV
def plot_validation_curves_grid(param, grid_cv_results_, ncol=3):
    
    param_list = set(grid_cv_results_['param_' + param].data)
    nrows = int(ceil(len(param_list)/ncol))
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=nrows, ncols=ncol, figsize=(18, nrows*6), sharex=True, sharey=True,
                             gridspec_kw={'wspace':0, 'hspace':0.1})
    
    for idx, x in enumerate(sorted(param_list)):
        mask = grid_cv_results_['param_' + param].data == x
        train_mu, train_std = grid_cv_results_['mean_train_score'][mask], grid_cv_results_['std_train_score'][mask]
        valid_mu, valid_std = grid_cv_results_['mean_test_score'][mask], grid_cv_results_['std_test_score'][mask]
        
        train_line = axes.ravel()[idx].plot(train_mu, '-', color='green',
                                            label='train: mean=${0:.3f}$, max=${1:.3f}$'
                                            .format(train_mu.mean(), max(train_mu + train_std)))
        valid_line = axes.ravel()[idx].plot(valid_mu, '-', color='red',
                                            label='test: mean=${0:.3f}$, max=${1:.3f}$'
                                            .format(valid_mu.mean(), max(valid_mu + valid_std)))
        
        axes.ravel()[idx].fill_between(range(0,train_mu.shape[0]), train_mu - train_std, train_mu + train_std, edgecolor='none',
                         facecolor=train_line[0].get_color(), alpha=0.3)
        axes.ravel()[idx].fill_between(range(0,valid_mu.shape[0]), valid_mu - valid_std, valid_mu + valid_std, edgecolor='none',
                         facecolor=valid_line[0].get_color(), alpha=0.3)
        axes.ravel()[idx].legend()
        axes.ravel()[idx].set_title('{0}=${1}$'.format(param, x))
